    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm a bit confused. you mentioned pseudonymization in that list. usually pseudonymization means there's still a way to re-identify someone if you have the right key or extra data. if a researcher took this dataset and combined it with a public voter registration list, could they potentially deanonymize a specific person? if there's even a small risk, i need to know so i can report it correctly.",
